data.text:
Nasir bin Olu Dara Jones (born September 14, 1973), better known by his stage name Nas, is an American rapper. Rooted in East Coast hip hop, he is regarded as one of the greatest rappers of all time. In Billboard and Vibe's "50 Greatest Rappers of All Time," he was listed at No.3. They remarked upon his "vivid storytelling," "precocious diction," and "longevity and adaptability."[1]
